connections.comments: Authenticates requests to Amazon SES using an API Key and API Secret

inputs.comments: An AWS IAM Access Key ID
inputs.label: Access Key ID

inputs.comments: An AWS IAM Secret Access Key

documentation.description:
An AWS IAM [access key pair](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/IAM/latest/UserGuide/id_credentials_access-keys.html) is required to interact with Amazon SES.
Make sure that the key pair you generate in AWS has proper permissions to the SES resources you want to access.
Read about Amazon SES IAM policies in the [AWS docs](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ses/latest/dg/control-user-access.html).

display.label: Send Email
display.description: Send an email through Amazon SES

inputs.comments: AWS provides services in multiple regions, like us-west-2 or eu-east-1. AWS region indicates the region in which your Identities are stored.
inputs.label: AWS Region

inputs.comments: The destination for this email. The recipients to place on the To: line of the message.
inputs.label: To Address

inputs.comments: The destination for this email. The recipients to place on the CC: line of the message.
inputs.label: Cc Address

inputs.comments: The destination for this email. The recipients to place on the BCC: line of the message.
inputs.label: Bcc Address

inputs.comments: The email address that is sending the email. This email address must be either individually verified with Amazon SES, or from a domain that has been verified with Amazon SES.
inputs.label: Sender Email

inputs.comments: The reply-to email address(es) for the message. If the recipient replies to the message, each reply-to address will receive the reply. This email address must be either individually verified with Amazon SES, or from a domain that has been verified with Amazon SES.
inputs.label: Reply To

inputs.comments: The subject of the message: A short summary of the content, which will appear in the recipient's inbox.
inputs.label: Subject

inputs.comments: The content of the message, in text format. Use this for text-based email clients, or clients on high-latency networks (such as mobile devices).
inputs.label: Text

inputs.comments: The content of the message, in HTML format. Use this for email clients that can process HTML. You can include clickable links, formatted text, and much more in an HTML message.
inputs.label: Html

inputs.comments: Specify a file name as the key (i.e. 'my-file.pdf'), and the file as the value
inputs.label: Attachments

documentation.description:
[Amazon SES](https://aws.amazon.com/ses/) is a service that enables developers to send mail from within any application.
The Amazon SES component allows you to list identities, and send emails to those identities.
documentation.dev:
:::note You must validate email addresses or domains
Before you can send an email using Amazon SES, you must verify that you are the owner of the email address or domain that you want to send email from.
You can do that from the SES admin page on the AWS console.
:::
